@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### List all expenses
GET {{baseUrl}}/expenses

### Create expense (valid)
# @name createExpense
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Cafe con medialunas",
  "amount": 3500,
  "category": "food"
}

### Create expense with explicit date
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "Monthly bus pass",
  "amount": 12000,
  "category": "transport",
  "date": "2026-07-01T00:00:00.000Z"
}

### Get expense by id (uses the id from "Create expense (valid)")
GET {{baseUrl}}/expenses/{{createExpense.response.body._id}}

### Update expense (partial)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/expenses/{{createExpense.response.body._id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "amount": 4200
}

### Delete expense
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/expenses/{{createExpense.response.body._id}}

###
### Error cases — each one exercises a different branch of the error handler
###

### 400 - Zod validation (empty description, negative amount, unknown category)
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "description": "",
  "amount": -5,
  "category": "crypto"
}

### 400 - Broken JSON body (body-parser SyntaxError)
POST {{baseUrl}}/expenses
Content-Type: application/json

{ broken

### 400 - Invalid id format (Mongoose CastError)
GET {{baseUrl}}/expenses/abc

### 404 - Valid ObjectId that does not exist
GET {{baseUrl}}/expenses/000000000000000000000000

### 400 - Update with invalid category (runValidators)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/expenses/000000000000000000000000
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "category": "crypto"
}


### Category summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/expenses/summary
